ABUJA – The All Progressives Congress (APC) has released updated list of 20 Subcommittees for inauguration on Monday March 7, to cater for various duties ahead of its coming National Convention. The Sub-committees are the Central Coordinating Committee made of 12 members of the APC Caretaker Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) and headed by Governor Mai Mala Buni, a secretariat of 8 members and 88- members screening Committee headed by Governor AbdulRazak AbdulRahman of Kwara state, a Screening Appeal Committee headed by Hope Uzodinma of Imo State. Others are Election/Planning Committee led by Gov Aminu Masari, Election Appeal Committee chaired by Gov Dapo Abiodun, legal Committee- Abubakar Malami, Accommodation- Bello Matawalle, Venue -Gov David Umahi, Transportation/Logistic- Simon Lalong, and Media/Publicity headed by Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu with Femi Fani-Kayode serving as Deputy Chairman. Groups Urge INEC To Review Ogoja/Yala Federal Constituency… 2023: It’s Unfair Igbos Have Not Been Considered For… Others are Security led by Yahaya Bello, Accreditation headed by Deputy Senate President, Senator Ovie Omo-Agege, Entertainment/ Welfare- Ahmed Idris Wase, Budget- Inuwa Yahaya, Finance- Abubakar Badaru, Accreditation of Volunteers/ Diplomats/Diaspora headed by Abdullahi Umar Ganduje, Digital Communication, Nasir El-Rufai, Convention Legacy/Rapporteurs, Governor Umaru Zulum.